  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [x] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Intel)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nI wrote a script to claim Arbitrum airdrop from their [TokenDistributor](https://arbiscan.io/address/0x67a24ce4321ab3af51c2d0a4801c3e111d88c9d9#code)\r\n\r\nHowever, on the claiming hour, the `claim()` function call failed for my script with\r\n`TokenDistributor: claim ended`\r\n\r\nIf you look at the TokenDistributor source code, then this error makes sense:\r\n```solidity\r\nrequire(block.number < claimPeriodEnd, \"TokenDistributor: claim ended\");\r\n```\r\nTheir `claimPeriodEnd` is 18208000 uint256, but the latest block is [73375296](https://arbiscan.io/blocks). So this revert makes sense.\r\n\r\nHowever, if I used the same contract to claim with js or with metamask, then claiming worked. You can clearly see from the contract that [claiming tx-s](https://arbiscan.io/tx/0x9e524f7491939f1f80475c168e1717564b282308569c4475a022e45cce1e6a66) work.\r\n\r\nWhy does metamask and ethers.js succeed, but forge script does not?\r\n\r\n\r\nHere is my script:\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\nimport { console2 } from \"forge-std/console2.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Run is Script {\r\n    function setUp() public {}\r\n\r\n    function run() external {\r\n        vm.startBroadcast();\r\n      \r\n        ArbAirDrop airDrop = ArbAirDrop(0x67a24CE4321aB3aF51c2D0a4801c3E111D88C9d9);\r\n\r\n        // correct 625000000000000000000\r\n        airDrop.claimableTokens(0xe5B1B7295B3A82d5eD9d16Cf3c79Ad0316Efa279);\r\n        console2.log(block.number);\r\n        console2.log(uint(airDrop.claimPeriodEnd()));\r\n        \r\n        // airDrop.claimPeriodEnd() = around 18000000\r\n        // but block.timestamp is 73094372.\r\n\r\n        // doesnt work with neither interface call, or address.call\r\n        // airDrop.claim();\r\n        0x67a24CE4321aB3aF51c2D0a4801c3E111D88C9d9.call(abi.encodeWithSignature(\"claim()\"));\r\n\r\n        vm.stopBroadcast();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface ArbAirDrop {\r\n    function claim() external;\r\n    function claimableTokens(address owner) external view returns (uint);\r\n    function claimPeriodEnd() external returns (uint);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI called it with my alchemy rpc (tried it also with arbitrum's public rpc)\r\n```\r\nforge script script/claimArb/ClaimArb.s.sol:Run \\\r\n  --rpc-url https://arb-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/my-access-token \\\r\n  --ledger \\\r\n  --sender 0xme \\\r\n  --broadcast \\\r\n  -vvvv\r\n```",
